In a speech to the House Democratic Caucus, President Biden expressed gratitude for Speaker Nancy Pelosi's leadership and praised her as a kind but tough leader. He emphasized the urgency of addressing the challenges faced by the American people, including the COVID-19 pandemic, economic recovery, healthcare, climate change, and institutional racism. The President urged the caucus to continue speaking up about the American Rescue Plan, highlighting its broad popularity among Americans. He also emphasized the need to explain and promote the plan to restore faith in government. President Biden expressed confidence that by delivering on the American Rescue Plan, it would build momentum and enable the achievement of other goals. He thanked the caucus for their work and expressed a willingness to answer questions.